sp.l:
It's a damn'd long, dark, boggy, dirty, dangerous way. Stingo, tell the gentlemen the way to Mr. Hardcastle's;
(winking upon the Landlord)
Mr. Hardcastle's, of Quagmire Marsh, you understand me.

By heaven, she weeps. This is the first mark of tenderness I ever had from a modest woman, and it touches me;
(to her)
Excuse me, my lovely girl, you are the only part of the family I leave with reluctance. But to be plain with you, the difference of our birth, fortune and education, make an honourable connexion impossible; and I can never harbour a thought of seducing simplicity that trusted in my honour, or bringing ruin upon one, whose only fault was being too lovely.
